            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onions </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p><p>Once the potatoes have had 10 min, add the <strong>carrot</strong> <strong>batons</strong> to one side of a separate baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and put in oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
