    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the<strong> beef stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in the<strong> Henderson's Relish</strong></p><p>Once the onions have softened, add 2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>beef stock</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>onion</strong> <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
